  "equal_fn_def": "// Generated equal-fn for determinism check.\n// Policy: errs_equivalent=True, opaque_ok=False\nspec fn det_set_self_fast_equal(r1: (), r2: (), post1_self_: Registers, post2_self_: Registers) -> bool {\n    (r1 == r2)\n    && ((post1_self_.r15 == post2_self_.r15) && (post1_self_.r14 == post2_self_.r14) && (post1_self_.r13 == post2_self_.r13) && (post1_self_.r12 == post2_self_.r12) && (post1_self_.rbp == post2_self_.rbp) && (post1_self_.rbx == post2_self_.rbx) && (post1_self_.r11 == post2_self_.r11) && (post1_self_.r10 == post2_self_.r10) && (post1_self_.r9 == post2_self_.r9) && (post1_self_.r8 == post2_self_.r8) && (post1_self_.rcx == post2_self_.rcx) && (post1_self_.rdx == post2_self_.rdx) && (post1_self_.rsi == post2_self_.rsi) && (post1_self_.rdi == post2_self_.rdi) && (post1_self_.rax == post2_self_.rax) && (post1_self_.error_code == post2_self_.error_code) && (post1_self_.rip == post2_self_.rip) && (post1_self_.cs == post2_self_.cs) && (post1_self_.flags == post2_self_.flags) && (post1_self_.rsp == post2_self_.rsp) && (post1_self_.ss == post2_self_.ss))\n}",
